content.description: If you like a good one move wonder and then low angle BS over a possible a** full of yucca spines this one is fer YOU!
content.protection: All of it.  Bring it all.
content.location: Hidden deep in the belly of First Ascent Land, you'll need yer best bramble scrambling skills.  Follow the trail past an easy handcrack that you'll post on instagram with insane photo-tilt to make it look worthy, and then past the rusty hangers (ignore) and head left.

content.description: HOHMANN how lucky to find this gem, can't believe someone put bolts at the top and then left it for us to get the FA!  Splitter braj!  Awkward start to solid hand jams in a flare lead to worming your way up through widening cracks and friable rock.  WUTS NOT TO LOVE NAWMEAN?!?
content.protection: single rack through 5" would cover you jest fine
content.location: This bad boy is deep in the heart of F.A.L. right down the hill from the rusted hanger guarding another FA for someone strong!  Pass up the ole worm crack and keep heading down hill, don't bust your ass on the slippery slab by the OW broulder problem you aren't strong enough to crank NO WORRIES BRO LOCALS ONLY
